%h1
  Upgrading RVM
%p
  RVM supports two ways of upgrading itself: one to the latest released version
  and the other to the latest repository version.
%h3
  To upgrade to the most recent release version
%pre.code
  :preserve
    $ rvm get latest
%p
  installs the latest released version.
%h3
  Upgrading to the latest repository source version (the most bugfixes)
%pre.code
  :preserve
    $ rvm get head
%p
  obtains the latest RVM repository version by using git, then running ./install
  from the cloned repository.

